bakshee
Homonym Number:
Word Class: adjective
Sense Number:
Definition:usu. senses in NZ `free'; `unofficial' f. orig. military <i>baksheesh</i>, `a tip', popularised in WW1 and WW2. .bds;1. (WW1) bakshee lance-jack <i>a lance-corporal.</i>
