Quote:  <i>Bakshee lance-jack</i>. A lance-corporal: military (esp. Australians' and New Zealanders'): in G.W. 2. Spg <i>Bakchsceach</i> [? F. WW1 : reference here to 1920s.]

bakshee leave unofficial or unapproved leave.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1960
Source:  Memories of Maoriland
Author:  SCRYMGEOUR
Vol / Page:  122
Edition:
Quote:  The ride down [on business] was uneventful, and though the `Electricity Station' [where a pair of good-looking girls lived] was only a few miles off the bridle track, Jim like a good Anzac, faithfully refrained from taking `Bachsceach Leave' and held to the paths of duty, that led in this case `not to glory, but nearly to the grave'.
